>(1) Regarding the origin of modern "de aru", (a) the medieval "de aru" was often used as "da-ji (jisha)" in the late medieval period, and accordingly the final form "de aru" disappeared at the beginning of the early modern period. (b) The medieval "de aru" was frequently used in the early modern period in lectures by Chinese scholars, colloquial translations by national scholars, and sermons by Buddhist monks, and continued to be used as a term by the educated class during the Edo period (1603-1867). There are two theories.
